186.8	Edward_Tufte	Edward Tufte	Edward Rolf Tufte (born 1942) is an American statistician and professor emeritus of political science, statistics, and computer science at Yale University. He is noted for his writings on information design and as a pioneer in the field of data visualization.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f4/Edware_Tufte_giving_a_class.jpg/220px-Edware_Tufte_giving_a_class.jpg
